# 💰 Expense Tracker App

A command-line expense tracking application built while learning Python fundamentals such as dictionaries, functions, loops, file handling, exception handling, and persistent data storage.

This application allows users to record expenses, search previous expenses, calculate total spending, and store expense data locally so it remains available even after the program is closed.

---

## 📌 Project Overview

This project helps users keep track of their expenses by storing expense categories along with the amount spent.

The application saves all expense data in a local text file, allowing previously stored data to be loaded again whenever the program is restarted.

The project was built to practice working with structured data, persistent storage, user input validation, and organizing code using functions.

---

## ✨ Features

* Add new expense entries
* Automatically update existing expense categories
* View all recorded expenses
* Search expenses by category
* Calculate total amount spent
* Reset all stored expense data
* Persistent data storage using file handling
* Automatic saving after every update
* Error handling for invalid user input
* Input cleanup using `.strip()` and `.lower()`

